			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Improved Reclaim Energy: 
<br />

<br />
Your solution is overpowering. Think of what Mages can do if they can chain pets without losing any mana, and if they do, turn it off and get mana at FT200+ rate. Bad idea. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Overpowering?  No.
<br />

<br />
FT200 means 200 mana EVERY SINGLE tick.  Sure, you could spend all your on-line time doing pet canni, but you would do ZERO DPS.  A more realisitic FT figure for pet canni is maybe FT200 for 5 to 10 min of every hour (that seems like a lot to me really).
<br />

<br />
If you spend 5 min per hour doing pet canni (at 200 mana per tick) you have earned yourself FT16.6.  10 min per hour = FT33.3.  Compare that to Necros getting FT50 from lich, or wizards getting FT23 with familiar and harvest AAs.  Keep in mind we incur substantial down time to regain that mana while they do not.
<br />

<br />
Not to mention that chaining pets endlessly with IRE is pathetic DPS.  A necro has more sustained DPS using root and a single dot, and they can keep this up for forever with less risk than a mage using IRE.
<br />

<br />
IRE is just plain and simple, a terrible AA.  It makes those who bought it feel like cripples because it hurts them more than it helps them, and it can't be reversed.  These potential fixes are reasonable and not overpowering.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
