			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Improved Reclaim revitalized the game for me, and gave me some things I would never have had I not invested in the skill. Mana pool independence when chaining pets is absolutely huge for me. AA point for AA point, Improved reclaim gives the biggest return on the investment. It is the only skill on our AA list that for only 3 points can alter our playstyle and eliminate downtime.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I respect the heck outta manaless chaining of pets, but I don't respect the fact that IRE still brings down the usefulness of another ability my class has.  No AA in the game does that, except IRE.  No other class loses anything by buying any AA ability they have available to them.  Yes, IRE reinforces one part of my class--pet chaining--but in the process it also dampens pet canni a <span style="font-weight: bold">noticeable</span> amount.  If it never did anything to hurt pet canni, or any other ability of mine, I would have no qualms with IRE.  The honest truth is I don't chain pets very often--I dislike soloing and don't grind xp in groups of mostly pets anymore.  Any chance I get, I jump into full pet groups, but surprisingly I am probably the ONLY IRE mage on Solusek Ro ATM.  I have enough AA's to keep me satisfied, and only ever log Boop on to do LDON for points or raids.  I hardly get to use the benefits of IRE as it stands, yet I am a very religious pet canni user.  Should I have to suffer for spending 3 AA points and choke on the fact that it makes me a stronger pet chainer?  I would think not.  No AA should have adverse effects associated with simply buying the skill--period.
<br />

<br />
Again, I respect pet chaining, but it isn't for me.  You've always been a proponent of pet chaining, and I fully respect your opinions.  IRE made all the difference to you in the world, but your play style directly is affected and evolved from that AA.  I hardly use it, get very little benefit from having it, yet I suffer the consequences of buying the skill.  I've had the skill for almost a year now, and I'm still not impressed.  I've soloed a ton using it with pet chaining, but it didn't do much for me.  Yes, I've used every type of pet available to a 65 mage, but I couldn't get into that sort of play style.  The way I chain pets is only slowed down by stopping to reclaim a nearly dead pet (and relying on root to hold the foe down for the new pet).  I have my pets as fast casting as they will be, IRE, and all the whistles and bells that make up the chaining magi.  I just don't care for the technique, and have no need to sit down and solo much anymore.  When I did solo a lot, I was too in practice of my own version of pet chaining to really utilize IRE as much as you probably do.  I see the value of manaless soloing, but I see the extra mana gain from pet canni more worth it to me.      
<br />

<br />
All I'm asking is any repercussions for buying the AA are removed.  If that happened, Boop would be a happy gnome!<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
